HEADWORD: Pharyngobranchial
<hw>Pha*ryn`go*bran"chi*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pharynx</ets> + <ets>branchial</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the pharynx and the
branchi⟦ae⟧; -- applied especially to the dorsal elements in the
branchial arches of fishes. See <er>Pharyngeal</er>.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A pharyngobranchial, or upper pharyngeal, bone
or cartilage.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
